HEADWORD: Undecane
<hw>Un"de*cane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>undecim</ets> eleven.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A liquid
hydrocarbon, <chform>C11H24</chform>, of the methane series, found in
petroleum; -- so called from its containing eleven carbon atoms in the
molecule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

